Perfect. Below are the learner-facing packs for all four modules in Course 3, in a consistent, drop-in JSON format you can feed to your course generator. I kept each pack compact enough to use immediately, but rich enough to cover interactive text, slides, audio, mind maps, and labs.

> Note on pedagogy: each module explicitly uses Learn Your Way’s multi-representation pattern with immersive text, section quizzes, narrated slides, audio dialogs that surface misconceptions, and mind maps, adapted to level and interests. ([Google Research][1])

---

```json
{
  "module_id": "3.1",
  "title": "Data Types and Structures",
  "hours": 6,
  "objectives": [
    "Differentiate structured, semi-structured, and unstructured data",
    "Explain tables, keys, cardinality, and basic relational design",
    "Draft a 1-page data dictionary for a small dataset"
  ],
  "prerequisites": ["Course 1 and 2 or equivalent", "Basic spreadsheet familiarity"],
  "success_criteria": [
    "Correctly identify PK and FK in a two-table mini schema",
    "Accurately classify fields by type and format",
    "Submit a data dictionary aligned to minimal metadata elements"
  ],
  "personalization": {
    "interests": ["sports", "music", "food", "business"],
    "reading_level": "adaptive",
    "pace": "adaptive"
